湧.definition: to bubble up; to rush forth

湧出.definition: to gush; to gush out; to pour out

湧泉.definition: gushing spring; see 湧泉穴|涌泉穴[yong3quan2xue2]

湧泉穴.definition: (TCM) acupuncture point KI-1, located on the sole

湧溢.definition: to well up; to spill out (of water from a spring)

湧現.definition: to emerge in large numbers; to spring up; to emerge prominently

湧起.definition: to well up; to boil out; to bubble forth; to spurt

湧進.definition: to spill; to overflow (of water, crowds); to crowd (into a space)
